Note: ============================================================================
Note: PowerShell Special Constructs
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "emit_subexpression_start" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Emit start of PowerShell subexpression $()

    proc emit_dollar from emitter
    proc emit_left_paren from emitter

    Return 1
End Process

Process called "emit_subexpression_end" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Emit end of PowerShell subexpression

    proc emit_right_paren from emitter

    Return 1
End Process

Process called "emit_array_start" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Emit start of PowerShell array @()

    proc emit_at_sign from emitter
    proc emit_left_paren from emitter

    Return 1
End Process

Process called "emit_array_end" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Emit end of PowerShell array

    proc emit_right_paren from emitter

    Return 1
End Process

Process called "emit_hashtable_start" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Emit start of PowerShell hashtable @{}

    proc emit_at_sign from emitter
    proc emit_left_brace from emitter

    Return 1
End Process

Process called "emit_hashtable_end" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Emit end of PowerShell hashtable

    proc emit_right_brace from emitter

    Return 1
End Process

Process called "emit_script_block_start" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Emit start of PowerShell script block {}

    proc emit_left_brace from emitter

    Return 1
End Process

Process called "emit_script_block_end" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Emit end of PowerShell script block

    proc emit_right_brace from emitter

    Return 1
End Process

Process called "emit_parameter" takes emitter as Integer, name as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Emit PowerShell parameter (-ParameterName)

    proc emit_hyphen from emitter
    proc emit_string with emitter, name

    Return 1
End Process

Process called "emit_variable" takes emitter as Integer, name as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Emit PowerShell variable ($variableName)

    proc emit_dollar from emitter
    proc emit_string with emitter, name

    Return 1
End Process

Process called "emit_pipeline_separator" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Emit pipeline separator with proper spacing

    proc emit_space from emitter
    proc emit_pipe from emitter
    proc emit_space from emitter

    Return 1
End Process

Process called "emit_assignment_operator" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Emit assignment operator with proper spacing

    proc emit_space from emitter
    proc emit_equals from emitter
    proc emit_space from emitter

    Return 1
End Process

